                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12578657" author="jorgenlo" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2008 09:11:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The log shipper thread also has to be restarted when the network has been reestablished since the log shipper thread will terminate if the socket is shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12584102" author="narayanan" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2008 10:44:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have modified the handleException method to return the transmitter&lt;br/&gt;
object that is created.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The log shipper bases its decision on whether it should continue with the&lt;br/&gt;
log shipping based on if a valid transmitter object is created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12585083" author="oysteing" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2008 12:43:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Narayanan. Patch looks good.  Committed to trunk at revision 644291.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
